        Conference of the United Church of Christ added to the collection by Zachary Bodnar, April
        2026.</p>
    </processinfo>
    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The church was first gathered in 1876 under the leadership of Andrew Brotherstone. In 1894,
        the Waveland Avenue Congregationalist Church officially joined the associated Chicago area
        Congregationalist churches. In 1961, the church joined the United Church of Christ. The
        church served its community until 1982 when it permanently closed.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The Waveland Avenue Congregational Church records include board reports, meeting minutes of
        the prudential committee, financial records, church meeting minutes and administrative
        records, church calendars and scheduling information, and the church's constitution.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>This collection has been arranged chronologically by start date.</p>
    </arrangement>
